11/03/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police announced on Wednesday (March 10th) the arrests of 23 hackers linked to the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK), who attacked more than 300 Turkish websites.
The arrests, which spanned 13 provinces simultaneously, followed a five month investigation.
Five of those in custody are under 18.
All have been charged with membership in the terror organisation.
(Sabah - 11/03/10;
Radikal, Hurriyet - 10/03/10)
